- **LIMIT 1 only when one result is asked for.** "Which races did X win?" → ALL rows. "List X that Y" → ALL rows. Only use LIMIT 1 for "the top", "the best", "the single highest/lowest".
- "Top N in each X" or word "rank" → **MUST** use `RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY ... ORDER BY ...)` (never `DENSE_RANK()`) in a subquery, then filter the rank. Do NOT add `IS NOT NULL` filters to the ranking column.
